cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.CG, cs.MM 

The paper deals with shape registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of unit vectors to encode non-Euclidean information suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of cost functions and estimation of transformations suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), computational geometry (cs.CG), or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
